<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Court2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Court,</orth> vb., to endeavour to please, to seek favour by blandishments; 1) absolutely: <cit><quote>I have forgot to c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.85" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. III, 1, 85</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>their purpose is to parle, to c. and dance,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.122" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 122</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>see how they kiss and c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.2.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 2, 27</bibl></cit>. Followed by <emph>it</emph>: <cit><quote>knows to c. it with words,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.1.91" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 1, 91</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) trans.: <cit><quote>did c. the lad with many a lovely look,</quote> <bibl n="shak. pp 45" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 45</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a most auspicious star, whose influence if now I c. not,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.183" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 183</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.244" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 244</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.131" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 131</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.1.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 1, 54</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.137" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 137</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 3.1.49" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.2.34" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.864" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 864</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.15" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 1, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.3.142" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 3, 142</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 54</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.78" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 78</bibl> <emph>(I'll c. his favours;</emph> O. Edd. <cit><quote>count).</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 4.3.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 3, 57</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.2.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 2, 6</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>